This paper deals with training deep fully convolutional neural networks for semantic image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new architecture for brain segmentation, which involves machine learning techniques such as error corrective boosting and pre-training with auxiliary labels, indicating that it may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning for medical imaging, which could potentially place it in the sub-categories of neural engineering (cs.NE) or multimedia (cs.MM).
